    • handlePacket

      <T> void handlePacket(Player player, IPacketWrapper<T> packet, boolean fromClient)
      Handle a packet being fired from the server or received from the client. This method allows registered packet handlers to process the packet.
      Parameters:
      player - The Player associated with the packet.
      packet - The IPacketWrapper object being handled.
      fromClient - True if the packet is from the client, false if from the server.

    • handleMovementPacket

      <T> void handleMovementPacket(Player player, Location from, Location to, IPacketWrapper<T> packet, boolean rotation)
      Handle a movement-related packet. This method allows registered movement handlers to process the packet.
      Parameters:
      player - The Player associated with the packet.
      from - The location the player is moving from.
      to - The location the player is moving to.
      packet - The movement-related IPacketWrapper object being handled.
      rotation - True if the packet is rotation-related, false if movement-related.

    • shouldHandlePackets

      boolean shouldHandlePackets()
      Check if the API should handle incoming/outgoing packets.
      Returns:
      True if outgoing packets should be handled, false otherwise.
